    // 7. MACTAN HONEYMOON: ISLAND-HOPPING COUPLE THREE-DAY
    // ------------------------------------------------------------------
    [
        'source_url' => 'https://www.wanderingfeetofmine.com/mactan-honeymoon/',
        'source_blog_name' => 'Wandering Feet of Mine',
        'source_image_url' => null,
        'title' => 'Mactan Honeymoon: A Three-Day Island-Hopping Couple Plan',
        'slug' => 'mactan-honeymoon-island-hopping-couple-three-day',
        'excerpt' => 'A three-day Mactan honeymoon for couples flying into Cebu: Hilutungan and Caohagan island hop, a Cebu City heritage afternoon, and a slow last morning.',
        'content_html' => <<<'HTML'
<p>Mactan is the island connected to Cebu City by the Mandaue and Marcelo Fernan bridges, and the eastern coast facing the Olango reef is the resort row that most international couples use as a Philippine honeymoon base. The Mactan resort coast has the cleanest connections to the smaller islands of Hilutungan, Nalusuan, and Caohagan, which together make the standard couple island-hopping day. For a three-day Mactan honeymoon, the plan splits between the sea day, a Cebu city afternoon, and a slow last morning.</p>
<h2>Before You Fly</h2>
<p>Fly Manila to Mactan-Cebu International Airport, a one-hour 25-minute flight, with Cebu Pacific, Philippine Airlines, or AirAsia. The airport is on Mactan itself, 20 to 30 minutes by van to the resort row on the eastern coast. Most accommodations include the airport transfer for honeymoon bookings.</p>
<h2>Day 1: Arrive, Beach Walk, Sutukil Dinner</h2>
<p>Drop the bags by midday and skip any tour for the first afternoon. Walk the beach of your resort, swim the shallow lagoon if the tide is in, and nap. Late afternoon, take a tricycle or a Grab to the Mactan Shrine area for the Lapu-Lapu monument and the Magellan marker; the small park has Sutukil row (sugba-tula-kilaw, three Visayan cooking methods) where the kitchens grill, simmer, and ceviche your fish in one order.</p>
<p>The sutukil is the cleanest honeymoon dinner on Mactan because the fish is fresh from the market that morning and the seating is open-air. Order a kilo of fish to share, ask the kitchen to do half grilled, quarter kilawin, quarter tinola. Carry small bills.</p>
<h2>Day 2: Island-Hopping (Hilutungan, Nalusuan, Caohagan)</h2>
<p>Book a private banca for two through the resort or a Maribago-area agency. The standard couple route hits Hilutungan first for the marine-sanctuary snorkel (great fish density, decent coral, deeper water than the other islands), then Nalusuan for the sandbar walk at low tide, then Caohagan for the long-lunch beach stop. Caohagan is the small private island known for the giant clam farm and the open-air lunch the islanders cook on banana leaves.</p>
<p>Banca out by 8 AM, back by 3 PM. Reef shoes are needed for the Hilutungan stop; the entry is over a rocky shelf. Bring a dry bag, a hat, a rash guard, and a reef-safe sunscreen.</p>
<p>Back to the resort by mid-afternoon. Sunset walk on the beach, dinner at the resort or at a Maribago kitchen.</p>
<h2>Day 3: Cebu City Heritage Afternoon, Fly Out</h2>
<p>Slow breakfast at the resort. By mid-morning, take a Grab into Cebu City (45 minutes off-peak, 70 minutes in traffic) for the heritage triangle: Basilica del Santo Nino, Magellan's Cross, and Fort San Pedro. The three sites are within a five-minute walk of each other and the afternoon walk takes around 90 minutes total. Free entry at the cross and the basilica; small admission at Fort San Pedro.</p>
<p>Lunch at a Cebu carinderia for the local lechon experience. Carcar lechon is the gold standard but the city versions at the Cebu Original Lechon Belly area are fine for a quick couple lunch. Back to Mactan by 4 PM, fly out from Mactan-Cebu by early evening.</p>
<h2>Where to Stay</h2>
<p>The eastern Mactan coast (Maribago and Marigondon) is the main resort row. The southern Mactan coast near Punta Engano has the quieter properties. For a honeymoon, the Maribago side has the better island-hopping access and the easier Cebu City transfer. The Punta Engano side has more space and a quieter feel.</p>
<h2>Getting Around</h2>
<p>Grab works on Mactan and in Cebu City. Tricycles handle short hops within Maribago. For the islands, the bancas leave from Maribago Public Beach. For Cebu City, Grab is the cleanest option for couples on a tight schedule.</p>
<h2>When to Go</h2>
<p>March to June is the calmest sea window with the best island-hopping visibility. November to February is the cool dry window with the cleanest evenings. July to October is the habagat side; the islands still hop but the seas are choppier.</p>
<h2>Couple Notes</h2>
<p>Pre-book the banca through the resort if you want a couple-only run. The shared boats from the public beach pack 20 to 30 tourists and the lunch stop on Caohagan gets loud. The private rate is roughly four times the shared, but for a honeymoon it is the better spend. Order the danggit (dried rabbitfish) with garlic rice at any Mactan breakfast spot; the Cebu version is the one that travels best as pasalubong.</p>
