    // ------------------------------------------------------------------
    [
        'source_url' => 'https://www.thepoortraveler.net/cebu-to-bohol-onward/',
        'source_blog_name' => 'The Poor Traveler',
        'source_image_url' => null,
        'title' => 'Mactan-Cebu to Panglao: A Ferry and Direct-Flight Onward Read',
        'slug' => 'mactan-cebu-to-panglao-ferry-onward-read',
        'excerpt' => 'How to get from Mactan-Cebu airport to Panglao: direct flight, ferry from Cebu City to Tagbilaran, and the airport bus chain. Honest time budgets.',
        'content_html' => <<<'HTML'
<p>Mactan-Cebu International Airport is the main hub for the central Visayas, and most travelers heading to Panglao on Bohol arrive here either to connect to a direct flight to Panglao or to take the fast ferry from Cebu City to Tagbilaran. The choice depends on the flight schedule and the time of arrival. Here is the honest onward read.</p>
<h2>Option 1: Direct Flight to Panglao</h2>
<p>Cebu Pacific operates a direct Mactan-Cebu to Bohol-Panglao flight, typically once daily. The flight time is around 30 minutes plus boarding. From Mactan-Cebu, allow 90 minutes from international landing to domestic boarding gate; the inter-terminal walk is short but the security and the domestic check-in take time.</p>
<p>For travelers landing on an international flight that connects through Mactan, the direct domestic Cebu to Panglao flight is the fastest onward option. Pre-book the same airline's connecting flight to avoid the separate check-in.</p>
<h2>Option 2: Ferry from Cebu City to Tagbilaran</h2>
<p>From Mactan-Cebu airport to the Cebu Pier 1 ferry terminal is around 30 minutes by Grab off-peak, longer during traffic. From Pier 1, several fast ferry operators (OceanJet, Lite Ferries, 2GO) run the Cebu to Tagbilaran route. The fast ferry takes around 2 hours; the older RoRo ferry takes 4 hours.</p>
<p>From Tagbilaran port to Panglao is around 30 minutes by tricycle, taxi, or Grab. Total time from Mactan-Cebu to Panglao via the ferry is around 4 to 5 hours including the airport-pier transfer and the ferry crossing.</p>
<h2>Option 3: Boat from Mactan to Tubigon (Northern Bohol)</h2>
<p>For travelers heading to northern Bohol (Tubigon side), the OceanJet ferry from Mactan to Tubigon takes around 2 hours. From Tubigon to Panglao is another 90 minutes by land. This option is rarely used by Panglao-bound travelers because the Cebu City-Tagbilaran route is shorter and the southern Bohol roads are better.</p>
<h2>Direct Flight vs Ferry</h2>
<p>The direct flight is the fastest but the schedule is limited to one flight per day. The ferry option has multiple daily departures with more flexibility. For travelers on a tight onward connection, the direct flight is the safer pick if the flight times line up. For travelers with a half-day buffer, the ferry option is cheaper and adds the sea-crossing experience.</p>
<h2>Step-by-Step: Mactan-Cebu to Pier 1</h2>
<p>From the international arrivals at Mactan-Cebu, exit to the arrival lobby. Grab pickup is at the designated zone near the parking. Allow 10 to 20 minutes for the Grab wait during peak hours. The ride to Pier 1 takes 30 minutes off-peak via the Mactan-Marcelo Fernan bridge.</p>
<p>At Pier 1, the OceanJet counter is on the right side of the terminal. Tickets are sold for the next available departure or for advance bookings. Tickets include the terminal fee. Bring identification.</p>
<h2>Onboard the Fast Ferry</h2>
<p>The fast ferry has air-conditioned seating in tourist and business classes. The crossing takes around 2 hours through the Cebu-Bohol strait. Bring motion-sickness tablets if you are prone; the seas can be choppy during habagat months.</p>
<h2>Tagbilaran Port to Panglao</h2>
<p>From Tagbilaran port, take a Grab or a tricycle to your Panglao accommodation. Most Alona-area resorts arrange a pickup at the port for an additional fee. The drive across the two bridges to Panglao takes 30 to 45 minutes depending on the traffic.</p>
<h2>Common Mistakes</h2>
<p>Do not book a same-day connection that gives you less than three hours between the Mactan-Cebu landing and the next ferry departure. The Pier 1 traffic can extend the airport-to-pier transfer to 60 minutes during rush hour. For first-timers, allow a generous buffer.</p>
<p>Do not assume the OceanJet schedule is published accurately at all times. Schedule changes happen during habagat months when the seas force cancellations. Check the operator's website the night before for the next-day departure list.</p>
<h2>Return Transfer</h2>
<p>For the return from Panglao to Mactan-Cebu, take the morning ferry from Tagbilaran for an afternoon flight from Mactan. Allow 5 to 6 hours total from the Panglao hotel to the Mactan boarding gate. The reverse direct flight is around 90 minutes total from Panglao airport to Mactan international departure.</p>
